						<summary>

						<p>This records the purchase of a quarter (<hi rend="italic">vēli?</hi>) of land situated to the south of the temple by the temple authorities, which was set apart for the daily supply of four <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice (or paddy ?) for offerings to the god Pichchadēvar (Bhikshāṭana) during the two services.</p>						

